byline.original: By SUZANNE DALEY and ANEMONA HARTOCOLLIS

abstract: Seemingly abrupt change in position of Greek Prime Min Alexis Tsipras regarding nation's debt crisis leaves many citizens wondering whether he betrayed his principles or whether he succeeded in convincing creditors that debt load is unsustainable and must be reduced.
lead_paragraph: Greeks were struggling to process the news, gird themselves for further budget cutbacks and assess what they had gotten for their efforts to stand against the European orthodoxy.

headline.main: In Athens, Greeks Wonder Whether Tsipras Folded or Restored Dignity
headline.print_headline: In Athens, Greeks Wonder Whether Premier Folded or Restored Dignity
